<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<RelativeLayout
    xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#F1F6F9"
    tools:context=".lessons.Lesson6">

    <androidx.appcompat.widget.Toolbar
        android:id="@+id/toolbar"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="?attr/actionBarSize"
        android:background="#F1F6F9">
        <Button
            android:id="@+id/btn_back"
            android:background="@null"
            android:drawableStart="@drawable/btn_back"
            android:layout_width="48dp"
            android:layout_height="?attr/actionBarSize"
            android:contentDescription="@string/back_button"/>
        <TextView
            android:text="Lesson 6"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:layout_gravity="center"
            android:gravity="center"
            android:textColor="@color/black"
            android:layout_width="wrap_content"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
    </androidx.appcompat.widget.Toolbar>

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_below="@+id/toolbar"
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content">
        <LinearLayout
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content">
            <androidx.cardview.widget.CardView
                app:cardCornerRadius="16dp"
                app:cardElevation="0dp"
                android:layout_marginHorizontal="16dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                <LinearLayout
                    android:orientation="vertical"
                    android:padding="10dp"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="match_parent">
                    <LinearLayout
                        android:orientation="horizontal"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                        <TextView
                            android:text="Quarter 1 – Module 6:\n Solving Routine and Non-Routine Problems Involving Division Without or With Any of the Other Operations of Fractions and Mixed Fractions."
                            android:textSize="17sp"
                            android:paddingHorizontal="10dp"
                            android:paddingBottom="10dp"
                            android:textColor="@color/black"
                            android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_semi_bold"
                            android:layout_width="0dp"
                            android:layout_weight="1"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                        <Button
                            android:id="@+id/btn_tts"
                            android:text="Read"
                            android:textAlignment="textStart"
                            android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                            android:background="@drawable/btn_secondary_button"
                            android:drawableStart="@drawable/ic_mic_secondary"
                            android:drawablePadding="10dp"
                            android:paddingHorizontal="10dp"
                            android:layout_width="0dp"
                            android:layout_weight=".5"
                            android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                    </LinearLayout>

                    <ImageView
                        android:background="@color/light_gray"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="1dp"/>

                    <TextView
                        android:id="@+id/tv_lessons_description_one"
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                        android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_regular"
                        android:padding="10dp"
                        android:text="Routine Problem:\n\nProblem: Divide 3/4 by 1/2.\n\nSolution: To divide fractions, we need to multiply the dividend (the first fraction) by the reciprocal of the divisor (the second fraction). So, we have (3/4) ÷ (1/2) = (3/4) × (2/1) = 6/4 = 3/2. Therefore, 3/4 divided by 1/2 is equal to 3/2.\n\nNon-Routine Problem:\n\nProblem: Five friends are sharing a rectangular chocolate bar that measures 2 and 1/4 feet by 1 and 1/2 feet. If they want to divide it equally among themselves, how much chocolate will each friend get?\n\nSolution: To solve this problem, we need to divide a mixed fraction by a whole number. First, we convert the mixed fraction to an improper fraction: 2 and 1/4 = (8/4) + (1/4) = 9/4. Then, we divide the length and width separately.\n\nLength division: (9/4) ÷ 5 = 9/4 × (1/5) = 9/20 feet per friend.\n\nWidth division: (3/2) ÷ 5 = 3/2 × (1/5) = 3/10 feet per friend.\n\nTherefore, each friend will get a piece of chocolate that measures 9/20 feet by 3/10 feet.\n\nThese examples demonstrate the difference between routine and non-routine problems involving division with or without other operations of fractions and mixed fractions. Routine problems typically involve straightforward calculations, while non-routine problems require additional steps and may involve real-world scenarios." />

                    <TextView
                        android:text="Example:"
                        android:padding="10dp"
                        android:textColor="@color/black"
                        android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_semi_bold"
                        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                    <ImageView
                        android:layout_width="match_parent"
                        android:layout_height="250dp"
                        android:layout_gravity="center"
                        android:contentDescription="example"
                        android:src="@drawable/smple_mod6"/>
                </LinearLayout>
            </androidx.cardview.widget.CardView>

            <HorizontalScrollView
                android:id="@+id/horizontalScrollView"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                <LinearLayout
                    android:orientation="horizontal"
                    android:layout_width="match_parent"
                    android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                    <androidx.cardview.widget.CardView
                        app:cardCornerRadius="16dp"
                        app:cardElevation="0dp"
                        app:cardBackgroundColor="#ffffff"
                        android:layout_marginStart="16dp"
                        android:layout_marginEnd="8dp"
                        android:layout_width="300dp"
                        android:layout_weight="1"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                        <LinearLayout
                            android:orientation="vertical"
                            android:padding="16dp"
                            android:layout_width="match_parent"
                            android:layout_height="match_parent">
                            <TextView
                                android:text="Tutorial"
                                android:textSize="18sp"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="10dp"
                                android:paddingTop="10dp"
                                android:textColor="@color/black"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_semi_bold"
                                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                            <TextView
                                android:padding="10dp"
                                android:text="Are you struggling with the numbers mixing in your head? In this tutorial, we will guide you through the step-by-step process of this lesson!"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_regular"
                                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                            <Button
                                android:id="@+id/btn_watch_tutorial"
                                android:text="Watch Tutorial"
                                android:textColor="@color/black"
                                android:background="@drawable/btn_secondary_button"
                                android:drawablePadding="10dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginStart="8dp"
                                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                        </LinearLayout>
                    </androidx.cardview.widget.CardView>
                    <androidx.cardview.widget.CardView
                        app:cardCornerRadius="16dp"
                        app:cardElevation="0dp"
                        android:layout_marginStart="8dp"
                        android:layout_marginEnd="16dp"
                        android:layout_marginBottom="16dp"
                        android:layout_width="300dp"
                        android:layout_weight="1"
                        android:layout_height="wrap_content">
                        <LinearLayout
                            android:orientation="vertical"
                            android:padding="16dp"
                            android:background="@drawable/bg_gradient_quiz"
                            android:layout_width="match_parent"
                            android:layout_height="match_parent">
                            <TextView
                                android:text="Quizzes"
                                android:textSize="18sp"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="10dp"
                                android:paddingTop="10dp"
                                android:textColor="@color/white"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_semi_bold"
                                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                            <TextView
                                android:padding="10dp"
                                android:text="Now let's measure your problem-solving skills with the quiz composed of true or false and multiple-choice questions to assess your level of understanding."
                                android:textColor="#F3F3F3"
                                android:fontFamily="@font/poppins_regular"
                                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                            <Button
                                android:id="@+id/btn_start_quiz"
                                android:text="Start Quiz!"
                                android:textColor="@color/white"
                                android:background="@drawable/btn_primary_button"
                                android:drawablePadding="10dp"
                                android:layout_marginTop="10dp"
                                android:paddingHorizontal="16dp"
                                android:layout_marginStart="8dp"
                                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                                android:layout_height="wrap_content"/>
                        </LinearLayout>
                    </androidx.cardview.widget.CardView>

                </LinearLayout>
            </HorizontalScrollView>

        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>

</RelativeLayout>